      "timestep_posted": 43
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for a cheap set of wheels that still has some life left? This car isn\u2019t perfect and I\u2019d rather be upfront about that, but it\u2019s a solid budget-friendly option for someone who needs basic transportation without spending a fortune. It\u2019s got the kind of wear you\u2019d expect from an older, well-used vehicle, but for the right buyer it could make a handy commuter, first car, or little runaround. If you want something affordable and honest, this one is worth a look.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 43
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Strong-running driver with a durable powertrain, responsive automatic transmission, and plenty of usable life for someone who wants an affordable commuter or solid project base. Starts, idles, and moves out well, with good oil pressure, steady cooling, and a chassis that feels honest for its age. Not a showroom car and it does have cosmetic wear and age-related needs, but the fundamentals are there and it presents as a practical, budget-friendly vehicle with real upside. Great candidate for a daily, backup car, or weekend wrenching project.",
      "price": 6950.0,
